						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama year 45, Śārvari, Chaitra [14], Monday,</hi> corresponding probably to either <hi rend="bold">Monday, 15th March, A.D. 1120</hi> or <hi rend="bold">Monday, 29th March</hi> of the same year. It registers a gift of gold made by the Sixty Families to the god Mūlasthānadēva of <hi rend="bold">Posavoḷal.</hi> Nāgarāśi-Paṇḍita is stated to have received the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
